'''Lu Dachang''' ({{zh|鲁大昌}}) (1889–1962) courtesy name Songling ({{zh|嵩龄}}) was a [[Kuomintang]] general from Gansu. In 1911 he was in [[Shaanxi]] province. He went to [[Hunan]] province in 1915, where he was promoted to company commander. Returned to Gansu in 1921. Promoted in 1922 to commander of the Infantry 3rd Battalion of the 1st Regiment. In the spring of 1926, the [[Zhili clique]] attacked the [[Northwest Army]] defending [[Dingxi]]. Promoted in 1927 to commander of the regiment. In 1931, he was promoted to commander of the 14th Division of the National Revolutionary Army, in charge of [[Min County]], [[Longxi County, Gansu|Longxi County]], [[Wen County, Gansu|Wen County]], [[Wushan County, Gansu|Wushan County]], [[Xihe County]], [[Li County, Gansu|Li County]] and [[Gangu County]].
==Chinese Civil War==
In September 1935, Lu fought the forces of the [[Chinese Red Army]] led by [[Lin Biao]] and [[Nie Rongzhen]] in [[Gannan Tibetan Autonomous Prefecture|Gannan]]. On August 25, 1937, he executed the son and daughter-in-law of [[Tibet|Tibetan]] [[Tusi]] Yang Jiqing.
